<dl id="un3030i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="un3" href="#un3030">UN3: </a>  <a href="../../ff/unbs/un3all.htm#un3030i"> (VIII.A.5) 30(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Chloris, Nestor&apos;s mother</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">And I saw lovely <mark>Chloris</mark>, <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> she was queen of Pylos, and <mark>bare glorious children to her lord, Nestor</mark> and Chromius, and princely Periclymenus, and stately Pero too, the wonder of all men. <small> Homer, <a name="OHBL" href="/udra/udex.htm#ohbl"><cite title="source">The Odyssey</cite></a>, trans. Butcher &amp; Lang (1906), 180f</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
